<td width="10"><img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/Message.gif" border="0"></td><td width="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000"> <b>Dave's post promted me to share my thoughts.</b> <img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/New.gif" border="0"></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000">Frustrated wizards please read this.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr></table><p><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER" bgcolor="000000">
<tr>
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" align="CENTER">
<tr bgcolor="999999">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td width="10"><img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/SmallNew.gif" border="0" alt="New Message"></td><td width="50%"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>Dave's post promted me to share my thoughts. (modified 0 times)</b> </font></td><td width="50%" align="RIGHT"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>Slyzone</b></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowProfile&ID=lynn&Board=wizard&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=0&Session=" target="Profile" OnMouseOver="window.status='View Slyzone (lynn) Profile.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Profile</font></a><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 "> | </font><a href="mailto:slyzone@provide.net" OnMouseOver="window.status='Send email to Slyzone.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Email</font></a></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">~chuckles~  I like that idea, porting stike.  I never thought of that one.  Wow.. I didn't mean to make this so long, but I think that you might find some of this helpful if you don't already use these suggestions.<p>

I would like to start with saying that Wizards are one of the most frustrating classes to play.  Cast and med circle is our life.  Thank god we loose the book at level 35, that is something to definately look forward to.<p>

I have been through the hassle of not being able to find a group.  But you have to remember, there are people that play a wizard right and others that do not.  The ones that do not cast with mana efficiency in mind and over nuke to early taunt the mob right off the tank and onto the nuker before the tanks and clerics no what is happening.  This is where you have to work on your own reputation of the kind of wizard you are.<p>

Now it took along time and several guild mates to help me learn what I think is the best approach to nuking and thought I would take this opportunity to share this.  ALWAYS assist the tank and through the first half the life of the mob stun or very small DD spells work well. By usuing the stun spells that you get later on, it gives the tanks free hits without receiving damage and gives the clerics a little less to heal. If you choose to you the small dd, this will more enlikely not get the mobs attention.  Now for what the wizzies do best, at the half way point of the mobs life, NUKE with a big bad DD spell and what a delightful feeling it is to see that you have delivered the final blow.  Now the tank is off to the next mob in line and here we go again.<p>

Now it takes a bit to get the timing down when to use that final DD cast.  For now you have 3 tanks, later you may have one.  There are some levels just before you get the new spells that you are lucky to have that big DD spell take a 1/4 of the health of the mob and I have casted twice in a row sometimes.  Sometimes, I am just patient and med until my stun is able to be recasted once again until that final point in health where I like to nuke hard.  Patience is the key in this circumstance.  Can't rush perfection. ~smiles~<p>

Let the tanks get a work out though.  We can blast through a mob and use a whole bar of mana to kill the mob.  But the tanks don't have to med when there is a cleric on duty and if the clerics have buffed properly and has a good enchanter, they are working on being mana effecient too.<p>

Using this appraoch you shouldn't have to use more than a bubble of mana at a time, and of course you are sitting on your butt between casts, therefore, you are able to gain mana during that time as well.<p>

Now for the subject of not being able to get a group.  I don't bother looking for a space in a group.  I create a group.  First me of course, second cleric, third enchanter.. from there tanks and casters will jump at the chance to join your group.  Casters need to stick together the tanks will follow.  The one thing that I would suggest to do though, is request a warning that someone is leaving so that you are able to fill the spot so the group doesn't fall apart.<p>

I do agree that I think that the other caster classes do have DD that can blast for about the same amount we do.  That frustrates me, for we are suppose to be proud of one of the few abilities that we have.  But I have been working my groups to suggest that all casters that are casting DD to cast at a certain level of health at a mob.<p>

Example:  Tank brings in an ugly to beat on and does it until it is 70% health.  I have a hot key that says, " C'mon NUKERS lets blast it to DEATH".  Then watch the fireworks begin.<p>

As in porting:  I think it is funny that wizards and druids can save a good hour+ of traveling for others, but they think we should port for 10pp..  ~chuckles~  What a joke.  From what I see the ports to Velious and Kanark go for a minimum of 50pp.  Now I do port for donation, but I might change that soon.  I have had people wanting me to leave my group to port them, the ones that I love is the nerve of offering 10 or 20 pp and half the time we are in the middle of a dungeon or somewhere that we ourselves will have to run forever to get back to.  That is if you really don't want to change your bind spot.<p>

I like the idea of the group deciding the amount of the port and when the port will take place.  That way, when I get back, I can share it with the group.  100pp spit six ways for me being gone for maybe 5 minutes at the most.  Is it really worth leaving the group?  I don't think so.  I usually reply that I am in a group and good luck finding a port out.<p>

Well, I hope that this is been helpful.  The lower levels of playing a wizard is a bytch.  But if you stick to it and look forward to the next time you get spells it is well worth it as grow in levels. Though I can solo, I find that it is more fun to have a group with a personality that you can chat making the time breeze by quickly. I find that there is less risks of dying within a group than soloing.  The higher the levels you gain the longer it takes to obtain the next level.  I am not into working on the same blue twice in my exp bar. <p>

If you approach it with having fun, you will find that the experience comes right along with it.  Happy Hunting.<p>

Slyzone 45th level wizard of Dragon's Blood guild.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
